ROWAN COUNTY, KENTUCKY, Appellant, v. WOODMEN OF THE WORLD, a Fraternal Benefit Corporation, Organized and Existing Under the Laws of Colorado, Appellee. No. 8335. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit June 27, 1940. Caldwell & Gray, of Ashland Ky., Richard M. Clay, of Morehead, Ky., Clyde L. Miller, of Louisa, Ky., and J. G. M. Robinson, of Ashland, Ky., for appellant. Nichols, Wood, Marx & Ginter, of Cincinnati, Ohio, for appellee.

Before HICKS,' SIMONS and HAMILTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

This cause was heard upon the transcript of the record, briefs and arguments of counsel, and it appearing to the Court that there is no reversible error upon the record, it is therefore ordered and adjudged that the judgment appealed from be and the same is in all things affirmed.
